=== v0.7.0 — M17 Managed Agents primitive correction — 2026-04-28 ===

Two Managed Agents primitives that were diagnosed at thinner-than-canonical
depth in earlier milestones (M13 Path C Files-API workspace skill files;
M14 per-session deb-set install via the bash tool) re-probed against the
live API and corrected. The 2026-04-28 re-probe surfaced that both
diagnoses had been wrong: config.packages on Environments is now accepted
with the documented {apt, cargo, gem, go, npm, pip} shape, and Skills API
endpoints had been returning 404 only because of a self-inflicted
wrong-beta-header bug — the canonical trio is
skills-2025-10-02,code-execution-2025-08-25,files-api-2025-04-14.

M17 trades the bash-tool deb-install workaround for env-baked packages
(cached across sessions sharing the same environment per docs) and
trades the Files-API workspace-skill-files workaround (Path C) for native
Skills resources attached to the agent via skills:[]. Routing skills are
now first-class workspace artifacts: queryable, versionable, auditable.

Operator-confirmed decisions (PLAN.md §Operator-confirmed decisions):
Q1 version: "latest" in agent body (auto-pickup of skill version-bumps);
Q2 networking unrestricted preserved (lockdown to limited deferred to a
separate hardening milestone); Q3 (a) bundle a per-skill foundations.md
Level-3 reference (each routing skill self-contained); Q4 retain
bl_setup_seed_skills_as_files through P8 then delete (safety net through
live-API integration); Q5 feature branch m17 (squash-merge to main on
M17 close).

Phase highlights (8 phases, 21 commits, +3315/-430 across 38 files):

P1 — Beta-header centralization. Three constants near top of
  src/bl.d/20-api.sh: BL_API_BETA_MA="managed-agents-2026-04-01",
  BL_API_BETA_FILES="files-api-2025-04-14",
  BL_API_BETA_SKILLS="skills-2025-10-02,code-execution-2025-08-25,files-api-2025-04-14".
  bl_api_call gains optional 4th arg beta_header (default $BL_API_BETA_MA).
  Three hardcoded "anthropic-beta:" sites replaced.

P2 — config.packages adoption. bl_setup_compose_env_body emits
  config.packages.apt with the canonical 9-package list (apache2,
  libapache2-mod-security2, modsecurity-crs, yara, jq, zstd, duckdb,
  pandoc, weasyprint). bl_setup_ensure_env detects packages drift via
  jq-sorted set equality on config.packages.apt; on mismatch creates a
  new env (renaming old to bl-curator-env-archive-<id>) and updates
  state.env_id. Networking remains unrestricted (Q2). The stale
  comment block stating "packages is NOT a valid field" deleted.

P3 — Routing-skills frontmatter + foundations bundle. Six
  routing-skills/<name>/SKILL.md files carry YAML frontmatter (name
  matches directory; description ≤1024 chars, leads with action verb,
  closes with "Use when …"). Six per-skill foundations.md created with
  IR-playbook lifecycle content (Q3 option a — Level-3 reference,
  bundled inside each skill's zip rather than hoisted inline or
  stripped). Description distinctiveness verified pairwise.

P4 — bl_setup_seed_skills_native + multipart helper.
  bl_api_call_multipart in 20-api.sh: single curl invocation, 1 retry on
  5xx, accepts files-array of <field>=@<file> entries.
  bl_setup_seed_skills_native in 84-setup.sh: per-skill compute sha256
  of SKILL.md + bundled files (sorted by path, hashed twice); compare to
  state.skills.<name>.sha256; skip on match, version-bump on
  existing-id, create-new on missing-id. Zip via command zip -r under
  BL_TMP_DIR. Description-size validation (>1024 chars → exit 65).
  bl_setup_seed_skills dispatcher routes to _native after probe success.
  tests/16-skills-native.bats new (8 tests); tests/helpers/skills-mock.bash
  shims curl against fixture responses.

P5 — agent.skills:[] + pdf attach + curator-agent.md prose trim.
  bl_setup_compose_agent_body emits skills:[] with 6 custom entries
  (each {type:"custom", skill_id, version:"latest"}) plus
  {type:"anthropic", skill_id:"pdf"}. resources:[] reference of old
  workspace skill files removed. bl_setup_ensure_agent compares
  state.agent.skill_versions to live agent skills array; CAS-bumps on
  drift. prompts/curator-agent.md §3.1 path-naming routing prose
  stripped (367 → 337 lines); replaced with a 2-line
  platform-routes-skills sentence + under-routing fallback. Q1
  version: "latest" gives auto-pickup of P4 version-bumps without
  agent recompose; trade against operator-controlled rollout
  acknowledged.

P6 — skills-gc — orphan archive + old workspace files.
  bl_setup_skills_gc(<mode>) cascade-deletes 3 v1 orphan skills
  (case-lifecycle, polyshell, modsec-patterns from 2026-04-23) by
  listing versions → DELETE per version → DELETE skill (cascade order
  mandatory per the 2026-04-28 probe; skill-delete with versions
  present returns 400). Lists workspace files filtered by
  scope.type="workspace" AND filename matching <routing-skill-name>-skill.md;
  DELETE per match. Wired only into bl setup --gc verb dispatch.
  dry-run mode logs intent without DELETE writes.

P7 — Cross-cutting test parity. tests/01-cli-surface.bats asserts
  bl setup --gc verb dispatches without help-text drift.
  tests/03-models.bats asserts BL_API_BETA_* constants exist + parity
  guard against future hardcoded "anthropic-beta:" reintroduction.
  tests/Dockerfile + tests/Dockerfile.rocky9 install zip and carry an
  explicit command -v zip sanity check (P4 dependency; pulled forward
  during P4 regression-fix sweep when full-matrix surfaced 18 failures
  due to missing zip in container images).

P8 — Live integration + ANTHROPIC notes rewrite + Path C dead-code
  removal. tests/live/setup-live.bats extended with M17 integration
  test gated by BL_LIVE=1 + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: asserts live env has
  config.packages with canonical 9-name list; asserts live agent has
  skills:[] with 6 custom (each version: "latest") + pdf; asserts each
  routing-skill display_title matches expected name.
  ANTHROPIC-API-NOTES.md §1 (Environments — packages) marked RESOLVED
  2026-04-28 with canonical accepted shape; §2 (Skills allowlist)
  rewritten to attribute the original 404 to wrong-beta-header
  self-inflicted gap, NOT Anthropic-side allowlist; canonical
  beta-header trio documented; original OPTIONS Allow: POST retained
  as historical record. §6 (?name= filter): re-probe note added —
  Anthropic now returns 400 with "unexpected query parameter: name"
  (improved diagnostic). New §11 captures research-preview-only
  Messages-API features that Managed Agents does not surface
  (cache_control, thinking). bl_setup_seed_skills_as_files function
