=== bl_observe_firewall comment-line filter — 2026-04-26 (Tier-2A e2e fixup) ===

apf /etc/apf/deny_hosts.rules and csf /etc/csf/csf.deny ship with multi-line
comment headers (## / # Trust based... / # Format of this file... / blank
separators) that the firewall collector previously emitted as bogus
firewall.rule records (rule="##", rule="# Trust based..."). End-to-end on a
host with apf installed produced 44 'firewall.rule' records of which ~30
were comments — pure bundle bloat consuming downstream skill context.

[Fix] src/bl.d/41-observe-collectors.sh — bl_observe_firewall rule-emit
      loop adds a `^[[:space:]]*#` skip alongside the existing blank-line
      skip. End-of-line `#` comments on real csf rules survive (line-start
      anchor only). bl-case attribution lives inside iptables/nft
      `comment "<tag>"` or natural rule lines, never as a leading-`#`
      header, so the filter does not lose case-tag correlation.
[New] tests/04-observe.bats — regression test 'comment + blank lines
      skipped (no rule="#..." bogus records)'. Stages an inline
      apf-style fixture mixing multi-line comment headers, blank
      separators, leading-whitespace comments, and three real IP
      entries (one with end-of-line `#` annotation). Asserts zero
      records with rule starting with `#`, exactly 3 firewall.rule
      records, and matching summary.total_records.
[Change] bl — regenerated from 27 parts via 'make bl'.

Verification: bash -n + shellcheck clean; make -C tests test-quick
green (33/33); 04-observe.bats full run green (83/83 including the
new regression at #62 and all 5 prior firewall tests).

=== bl_help_* alignment with live dispatchers — 2026-04-26 (Tier-1 e2e fixup) ===

End-to-end exercise of `bl` against tests/fixtures/ surfaced systemic drift
between every per-verb help block (in src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh) and the real
flag set its dispatcher accepts. Operators following `bl <verb> --help` were
hitting "unknown flag" / "missing <arg>" errors on flags the help advertised
but the impl never accepted. DESIGN.md §5.6 had already flagged case-help
drift as known-stale; this sweep extends the same correction to observe /
consult / run / defend / clean.

[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — bl_help_observe now matches collector
      flag sets: htaccess takes positional <dir> + [--recursive] (not
      --root <path>); fs --mtime-cluster takes positional <path> +
      --window <secs> (not --under <p> --cluster-window-secs N); sigs
      is [--scanner ...] enumeration (not --root --sigs scan); proc
      requires --user <user>; log journal --since is required + --grep
      replaces the non-existent --unit. file/log apache/log modsec/cron/
      firewall/bundle flag lists extended to match impl.
[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — bl_help_consult lists the three real
      modes (--new --trigger / --attach <id> / --sweep-mode --cve) per
      DESIGN.md §5.2; the prior 'bl consult "<case description>"' form
      was never accepted by the dispatcher.
[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — bl_help_run shows positional <step-id>,
      [--yes] [--dry-run] [--unsafe] [--explain], plus --list and
      --batch [--max <N>] forms. The prior --tier flag did not exist.
[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — bl_help_defend shows real per-backend
      forms (modsec <rule-file-or-id> [--remove], firewall <ip>
      [--backend ...], sig <sig-file> [--scanner ...]); --apply and
      operator-callable --rollback never existed in src/bl.d/82-defend.sh.
[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — bl_help_clean drops the dangerously
      misleading "unlink file (diff pre-shown, quarantine preserved)"
      kind line; per DESIGN.md §11 + src/bl.d/83-clean.sh:529 the file
      verb MOVES to quarantine and never unlinks. Replaced with the four
      real per-kind forms (htaccess/cron/proc/file) plus --undo /
      --unquarantine restore paths.
[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — bl_help_case drops the 'open <id>' and
      'note "..."' verb entries that DESIGN.md §5.6 explicitly tracked
      as known-stale; case allocation lives in 'bl consult --new' and
      notes append via the memstore path bl-case/<case>/<artifact>.md.
[Change] bl — regenerated from 27 parts via `make bl` after the help
      block edits; assembled artifact stays in sync with src/bl.d/.

Verification: bash -n + shellcheck clean; make -C tests test-quick
green (33/33 BATS — smoke + cli surface). No behavior changes in any
dispatcher; help-string text only.

=== M16 final fixup — 2026-04-26 (sentinel-review pass on full milestone; v0.6.0 stamp-up) ===

Final adversarial 4-pass review across the full M16 milestone surfaced 3 MAJOR
findings (all confirmed real by engineer FP check) plus 5 MINOR. This commit
folds the validated fixes plus the v0.6.0 stamp-up across README/PRD/DESIGN
and RPM/DEB packaging so the doc surface matches the binary version.

[Fix] src/bl.d/60-run.sh — bl_run_args_relative_to_iso adds BSD `date -r N`
      fallback after the GNU `date -d "@N"` form. The project's portability
      discipline (CLAUDE.md FreeBSD partial-target) requires BSD-paired calls
      anywhere `date -d` appears. Sentinel #2.1.
[Fix] src/bl.d/60-run.sh — bl_run_args_warn_unknown switches from
      case-glob to [[ literal substring ]] matching. Curator-emitted keys
      with shell-glob metacharacters ('path*', '[abc]') would have matched
      partial known-keys silently. Sentinel #1.3.
[Fix] src/bl.d/60-run.sh — comma-list fan-out in htaccess + fs_mtime_since
      adapters trims leading/trailing whitespace per element. Curator
      emissions like `roots="/var/www, /home/x"` previously passed
      " /home/x" (leading space) to the collector, causing confusing
      "not a directory" errors. Sentinel #2.4.
[Fix] src/bl.d/60-run.sh — known-keys lists extended for observe.file
      (sha256_check, size_threshold), observe.log_modsec (filters), and
      observe.firewall (breakdown_by) to match curator-observed semantic
      vocabulary from CASE-2026-0022 emissions. Suppresses warn-noise on
      already-recognized keys the collector ignores. Sentinel #1.2.
[Fix] src/bl.d/33-bridge.sh — bl_bridge_post_step skips pending
      re-creation when results/<step-id>.json already exists. Pre-fix:
      bridge re-fetched the same window after `bl run` deleted the pending
      entry, last-write-wins POSTed it back, next bridge tick re-ran the
      step → writeback HTTP 400 because curator session was already past
      the tool_use_id. Sentinel #2.3 — the most behaviorally significant
      fix in this round.
[Fix] src/bl.d/60-run.sh — bl_run_step writeback session-event POST now
      ledger-records `writeback_session_failed` on API failure instead
      of silently swallowing with `|| true`. Operator can now see in
      `bl case log` that the curator session diverged from local step
      state. Sentinel #3.3.
[Change] schemas/ledger-event.json — adds writeback_session_failed to
      the kind enum.
[Change] README.md, PRD.md, DESIGN.md — version stamp 0.5.2 → 0.6.0 to
      match BL_VERSION. README install-line example output, PRD title +
      target-release callouts, DESIGN target-release header. Sentinel #2.6.
[Change] pkg/rpm/blacklight.spec — version 0.5.2 → 0.6.0 + new changelog
      stanza for M16 milestone.
[Change] pkg/deb/debian/changelog — new 0.6.0-1 entry; existing 0.5.2-1
      entry preserved.
[New] tests/03-bridge.bats — regression test for results-skip:
      bridge with results/<step-id>.json present must NOT re-create
      pending/<step-id>.json. Existing 5 bridge tests had route-stack
      adjustments to add explicit results-not-found mocks since the new
      check-before-post path now executes on every bridge invocation.

DISCARDED: 1.4 outer-case-wrapper structural-only (demoted INFORMATIONAL),
1.5 unused `local rc` declarations (pattern-consistent with existing file),
2.5 duplicate-key collision (no test coverage; defensive only), 2.7
MEMORY.md P5 contribution undercounted (semantically accurate enough),
