=== v0.5.0 release — 2026-04-26 (M15 + post-M15 consolidation) ===

Live API correctness round 2 + integration-notes formalization.

Sessions events shape | 2026-04-26 — silent breaking change in upstream
      managed-agents-2026-04-01 beta surface. Bare-event payload
      ({type:"user.message", content:[…]}) was working through M12 P5.5
      (2026-04-25 last live-trace harness run); the {events:[…]} wrapper
      requirement surfaced 24h later during M15 P8 live integration smoke.
[Fix] src/bl.d/27-outbox.sh — outbox drain wraps stored wake payload in
      {events:[.]} via jq before POST /v1/sessions/<sid>/events.
[Fix] src/bl.d/50-consult.sh — bl_consult_register_curator wraps the
      direct-session wake event in {events:[…]}.
[Fix] src/bl.d/60-run.sh — bl_run step-result event wrapped in {events:[…]}.
[Fix] src/bl.d/70-case.sh — bl_case_close render-brief event wrapped in
      {events:[…]}.

Sessions.create body | 2026-04-26 — finalized field shape against the live
      API. Field is `agent` (not `agent_id`); `environment_id` is required;
      resources[] accepts entries shaped {type, file_id, mount_path}.
[Fix] src/bl.d/50-consult.sh — bl_consult_create_session reads env_id from
      state.json, fails fast with PREFLIGHT_FAIL if missing, includes both
      `agent` and `environment_id` in the create body alongside the
      resources[] array (8 corpus files + 6 skill-fallback files when
      Skills API is gated).
[Fix] src/bl.d/50-consult.sh — bl_consult_new retry limit raised from 3 to
      ${BL_CONSULT_ALLOC_MAX_RETRIES:-50}. Fresh workspace counters start at
      0 but shared-API-key memstores carry pre-existing case-id paths;
      every collision costs only a counter increment so 50 retries is
      strictly cheaper than failure.

Environments.create body | 2026-04-26 — public API surface accepts
      {name, config:{type:"cloud", networking:{type:"unrestricted"}}} only.
      The legacy {type:"cloud", packages:{apt:[…]}, networking:{…}} top-
      level shape returns 400 "Extra inputs are not permitted" for every
      field but `name`. apt-package install is now session-driven via the
      curator's bash tool until Anthropic exposes a setup-script field.
[Change] src/bl.d/84-setup.sh — bl_setup_compose_env_body emits the
      canonical nested-config body. networking:"unrestricted" preserves
      session ability to apt-install apache2 / mod_security2 / yara /
      duckdb / pandoc / weasyprint at runtime.
[Change] docs/setup-flow.md §4.3 — body shape rewritten with packages-as-
      Path-C-gap note; legacy body removed.

Skills API workspace-allowlist fallback | 2026-04-26 — /v1/skills returns
      404 for non-allowlisted workspaces. Probe distinguishes 404 (gated)
      from 401/403 (auth) and 5xx (transient).
[Change] src/bl.d/84-setup.sh — bl_setup_seed_skills probes /v1/skills
      with the body+status format ('\n%{http_code}'); on 404, falls
      through to bl_setup_seed_skills_as_files which uploads each
      routing-skills/<name>/SKILL.md as a corpus File at
      /skills/<name>-skill.md. Probe parsing is portable across real curl
      AND the test curl shim (tests/helpers/curator-mock.bash).

Preflight memstore-id seeding | 2026-04-26 — closes M15 fallout where
      consult/run verbs collapsed to literal "memstore_bl_case" default.
[Fix] src/bl.d/30-preflight.sh — BL_MEMSTORE_CASE_ID seeded from
      state.json (.case_memstores._default) BEFORE the cached-agent-id
      early-return path. Old per-key file (state/memstore-case-id) was
      removed during the M13 state-migration; per-verb fallbacks were
      reading the now-deleted file and resolving to the literal default.

Live integration smoke + fixture parity | 2026-04-26
[New] tests/live/setup-live.bats — BL_LIVE=1 gated; runs the full
      setup→check→consult→reset cycle against the real Anthropic
      workspace. 4/4 green. Test 3 (consult --new) extracts the allocated
      case-id via grep ... | tail -1 (not head -1) — earlier output lines
      may name OTHER cases (dedup-fingerprint warnings, materialize
      409 conflicts) so the trailing standalone case-id line is the only
      reliable anchor.
